{"type":"message","id":"010197d6","parentId":"c004e994","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:19:54.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see what happened clearly:\n\n1. **Asset bundle build was successful** - `BuildAssetBundles` completed in ~17 minutes with \"Build Successful\" messages\n2. **Bundle encryption completed successfully** - There's a log showing file encryption completed\n3. **CDN upload step had two issues:**\n   - `fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git` - The CDN git repo isn't configured locally\n   - `System.Net.WebException: The remote server returned an error: (404) Not Found.` - When trying to download a CDN file\n   - But it continued and created a local Server.json: `D:/cdn_solo\\update\\Android\\Test1\\1.0.44\\Config\\AB1\\Server.json`\n   - It says \"模式: 本地测试\" (Mode: local test)\n\nSo the pipeline seems to have:\n1. ✅ Build asset bundles successfully\n2. ✅ Encrypt bundles\n3. ⚠️ Failed to upload to CDN (git not configured, 404 on download attempt)  \n4. ✅ But set up local test environment (created Server.json at D:/cdn_solo/...)\n\nThe pipeline ran in \"本地测试\" (local test) mode. Since it's a test server update, maybe the local test mode setup is sufficient and the CDN upload isn't critical for testing? But let me check if the Unity process exited with an error or success.\n\nLet me check the process status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HuIEeSXSC6qH4yRPOVIh3329","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"delta-tidepool","action":"poll","timeout":5000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2372,"output":400,"cacheRead":18688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21460,"cost":{"input":0.00033208,"output":0.00011200000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000523264,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000967344}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778829588239,"responseId":"961c4f35-9ffd-44b6-8c36-572bd4e